# Terms of Service and License Information for NZQA Scholarship Search

Last Updated: 2024-09-28

## Overview

NZQA Scholarship Search is a free educational resource providing access to archived NZQA scholarship materials. This document outlines the terms of service for using our website and the license information for various components of our project.

## Website Components and Licenses

1. Website Code: GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0)
2. Archived Content: NZQA materials used under Fair Use principles

### 1. Website Code (GPL-3.0)

The source code for this website, excluding third-party libraries, is available under the GNU General Public License v3.0. You can find a copy of this license at: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.en.html

### 2. Archived NZQA Materials (Fair Use)

The NZQA scholarship materials archived on this website are the intellectual property of the New Zealand Qualifications Authority (NZQA). These materials are provided here for educational and research purposes under the principle of fair use.

## Terms of Use

By using NZQA Scholarship Search, you agree to the following terms:

1. Educational Use Only: The website and its contents are for educational and non-commercial use only.

2. No Redistribution: You may not redistribute, republish, or use the archived materials for commercial purposes without explicit permission from NZQA.

3. Attribution: When citing or referencing materials from this website, provide proper attribution to NZQA as the original source.

4. User Contributions: If you contribute to the website (e.g., through comments or submissions), you grant us a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license to use, modify, and distribute your contributions.

5. No Warranty: The website and its contents are provided "as is" without any warranties, express or implied.

6. Compliance: You agree to comply with all applicable copyright laws and these terms of use.

## Disclaimer

NZQA Scholarship Search is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or connected to NZQA. We do not claim ownership over the archived materials. Our purpose is solely to preserve and provide access to these educational resources.

## Changes to These Terms

We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Users are encouraged to check this page regularly for any changes. Your continued use of the website after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the modified terms.